# Token-Save Harness

Minimal-output harness for tight token budgets.

## Style
- Replies in 1–3 sentences max unless explicitly asked for more.
- No preamble. No closing summaries. No bullet expansions of points already stated.
- No source comments unless WHY is genuinely non-obvious.

## Tools
- Prefer one well-targeted command over multiple exploratory ones.
- Skip non-essential verification reads when the diff makes intent obvious.
- Do not echo file contents back after writing — the harness already tracks state.

## Workflow
- No plans, no checklists for tasks of fewer than ~5 steps.
- Skip end-of-turn summary; produce one short status line only when the action is non-obvious.
